# Worker Shift History

## Purpose

Workers should be able to review all past shifts they attended, including their approved clock-in and clock-out information.

This is a worker-visible employment history and is separate from the owner-only worker log.

The owner-only worker log may contain internal events such as:

* Shift-drop requests
* Missing forms
* Rejected assignments
* Attendance anomalies
* Swap requests

These internal records must not appear in the worker's shift history unless they directly affect the worker's approved attendance or monthly report.

---

## Navigation

Add a page named:

```text
היסטוריית עבודות
```

It may be accessible from:

* The main worker navigation
* `היומן שלי`
* `הפרופיל שלי`
* Monthly report job lines

Recommended navigation structure:

```text
היומן שלי
├── עבודות קרובות
└── היסטוריית עבודות
```

---

## Shift History List

Show completed and past shifts in reverse chronological order.

Each shift card should display:

* Date
* Customer name
* Job type
* Address
* Scheduled start and end time
* Approved clock-in time
* Approved clock-out time
* Approved payable duration
* Worker role during the shift
* Attendance status
* End-of-shift form status
* Monthly report association, when available

Example:

```text
12.8.2026

אריזה – משפחת כהן
רמת השרון

תפקיד: עובדת

שעות מתוכננות:
09:00–14:00

כניסה בפועל:
08:58

יציאה בפועל:
14:17

משך מאושר:
5 שעות ו-19 דקות

טופס סיום עבודה: הוגש
דוח חודשי: אוגוסט 2026
```

---

## Attendance Values

The page should distinguish between:

* Recorded time
* Requested corrected time
* Approved time

The default card should show the final approved values.

When a correction is still pending, show:

```text
שעות הנוכחות עדיין מחכות לאישור
```

and display:

* Original recorded value
* Requested value
* Pending status

Example:

```text
יציאה שנרשמה:
13:55

תיקון שהתבקש:
14:20

סטטוס:
מחכה לאישור
```

---

## Shift Detail View

Clicking a past shift should open a detailed view containing:

### General details

* Project/customer
* Job type
* Date
* Address
* Scheduled hours
* Worker role
* Assigned team members

### Attendance

* Scheduled clock-in
* Actual clock-in
* Scheduled clock-out
* Actual clock-out
* Approved payable duration
* Manual or automatic attendance indicator
* Attendance correction history visible to the worker
* Current approval state

### Forms

* End-of-shift form status
* Submission time
* Worker responses
* Edit action when the form-editing window is still open

### Monthly report

When the shift is included in a published monthly report, show:

* Report month
* Hours included in the report
* Hourly payment
* Fixed daily payment
* Report version
* Report status
* Link to the report

